The core is flowing, and the fuel is breached!§0§0§0 Once completed, if ur playing in hardcore mode use you sync shell to have extra lives. You have one life, and then you have to restart!

Get all the waste.

Tip #1: There is Ore Exevation

Yugospit is a planet full with pretty much waste blocks. Using some of the waste that resisdes around you, and you can turn 7 of them into 1 Plant Fibref. When can be used in the barrel you just made to make some dirt. And later a sapling for trees.

Trees are a natural resource that takes a long time to grow. It even takes longer in this wasteful enviroment. Using apples, wheat, or saplings you can get this still called Plant Matter which can automatically grow trees.
Use wood to make planks on the chopping block, and planks to make sticks. Use your bare fist for now, but later you can upgrade to an axe.
There comes a time when you are starving and need food. Well just drying rotten flesh will get you jurky.
Twerk twerk, twerk for trees.
Flint one of the Natural resources of this map. Well it more natural then those meters.
Whose the Tough guy now
String can be a very useful resource for future tools.
Heavy yet useful
This pick is very useful to get your first ores. To do so first make this pickaxe
This axe very fastly speeds up chopping while you are chopping up wood or sticks
Find a meteror then break in with your pickaxe. Despite the tooltip it is pretty fast to break in. Once inside, get some cobble. While your there grab some ores as well.
Combine 4 of any type of rock expect to make the cobble version of that stone.
Combine 4 Fragments into a clusters. Then Smelt it in the furnace, made with some cobble.
Crystals come raw. To process them u have to cut them!
Yugospit has a very high huminity level. There are some canteens on the wall there. Go take it and fill it up with water in the pool outside. That will be much better
Even though water is nice, it might be better if it is a little more pure. Combine the bottle or your canteen with this filter to purify it.
The rest from your very own bed will be useful to sleep through the dark nights on Yugospilt.
Now that you have access to wood, you can make this nifty tool called a crook. Pretty much it has a higher chance to get saplings from trees. It also give you a chance to get plant fibers.
Getting fibres is almost a joke now.
There is alot of waste on Yugospit. Lets turn some of them into useful wasteland barrels.
Obsidian is one of the materials in the meterors that needs a powerful pick to mine. Diamond is one of those tools. Crate a diamond pickaxe, and then get some obsidian. It will be useful.

This very hostile place, has some great materials that you might be looking for. Make sure you don't die. Suit up with enough stuff as you can, and only take what you need too. Your stuff might be there forever.
The Nether is a very dangerous place. Some iron armor can be very useful to protect yourself from the underworld.

Now that we have some basic primus dust we can make this nifty gadget. This allows you to make Alchemical Ore Dust using Alchemy. To do this you have to fuel it with primus and then put in the required materials to make that ore duct. There is JEI Integration for this.
Blazes are a monster in the nether. They can mostly be found near nether fortress. They drop precious blaze rods, that can be converted into blaze power which can be used for some stuff.

Primus is this weird type of dust that can be used for alot of the early game stuff in the Alchemy mod. If you dont know what that is, its a way to make metals out of different alchemical powders, which are made from different materials. The most basic one is done in a crafting table, yet later you will need a special block for this.
The basic tier of a condenser. This is the brain of the multiblock.
The frame for the casing. Make sure to give it a redstone signal.

These tools can be used to drop crystal fluid which we will make soon into the condensers, to produce the ore from the alchemical dust.

Keep Note: Before you place this you need to make a enclosed space for the droppers to point into that is above the casing. Glass is recommend so you can see inside. Corners are not needed.

Crucibles have a couple uses. The most important for metal creation is the melting of crystal shard into crystal fluid. Place these next to the upper Fluid Dropper. This will auto push the crystals into the dropper. Make sure that you only put 4 crystals in at a time. Otherwise it will not take them.

Also keep note 1 crucible will suffice but it is very slow. 3 is recommended.
The crucible inserted, can automatically insert crystal shards into a crucible. It is a very powerful block for a simple purpose, because it wont over put shards in.

Crystals can be dropped into crucible, but what about making crystals. 3 Fusion table can automatically make it but how to get it into the crucible inserted. Why using a item transport method of course. A hopper is a very good option but there is tons of other options
Alchemical Iron can be made in the Fusion table. Once done then you can drop it into the combustion block. Place a chest below it to collect the ingots.

The wooden stuff is good. Even the stone stuff is good, but the iron is a mid tier one. The higher your condenser and casings stats are the more ingots come out of a dust. Think of this like a complex addition problem. The dust isnt as effitient with wood, but can be increased with the iron. Meteror ores will suffice for this purpose
Secondus is another tier of dust. This will allow you to extract more dust from the fusion you did.
Tertius, the highest tier alchemical dust will allow you to get the most out of your fusion. Combindinding this with a high tier combustion heater will produce tons of metal!

Ahooy, you just crash on the planet Yugospit. This planet is full of waste and meteors with resources that crashed from Earth. Why not head out, explore but don't get too hot, thirsty or hungry, or you might die. Dieing is bad since your in hardcore mode, but with the power of sync shells, you can come back if u do so.
